punctuation marks used alphabetic languages around world. purpose punctuation mark meaningful grammatical relationships sentences aid readers understanding text indicate features important reading text aloud.[231] dialects, accents, varieties main articles: list dialects english language, world englishes, regional accents english dialectologists distinguish english dialects, regional varieties differ other terms grammar vocabulary, regional accents, distinguished different patterns pronunciation. major native dialects english often divided linguists two general categories british dialects (bre) north america (ame).[232] also exists grouping major native varieties english southern hemisphere, prominent australian new zealand english. uk ireland see also: english language england, northern england english, scots language, scottish english, welsh english, estuary english, ulster english, hiberno-english map showing main dialect regions uk ireland place english first evolved, british isles, particularly england, home variegated pattern dialects. within united kingdom, received pronunciation (rp), educated dialect south east england, traditionally used broadcast standard, considered prestigious british dialects. spread rp (also known bbc english) media caused many traditional dialects rural england recede, youths adopt traits prestige variety instead traits local dialects. time survey english dialects, grammar vocabulary differed across country, process lexical attrition led variation disappear.[233] nonetheless attrition mostly affected dialectal variation grammar vocabulary, fact 3 percent english population actually speak rp, remainder speaking regional accents dialects varying degrees rp influence.[234] also variability within rp, particularly along class lines upper middle class rp speakers native rp speakers speakers adopt rp later life.[235] within britain also considerable variation along lines social class, some traits though exceedingly common considered "non-s